'serif';font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;&gt;&lt;span style=visibility:hidden;&gt;&#x200b;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;p style=font-family:'Times New Roman'
'Times'
&lt;p style=font-family:'Times New Roman'
'Times'
'serif';font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;&gt;&lt;span style=visibility:hidden;&gt;&#x200b;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=font-family:'Times New Roman'
'Times'
'serif';font-size:10pt;text-align:justify;margin:0pt;&gt;NOTE 11&#x2014;DERIVATIVE INSTRUMENTS AND HEDGING ACTIVITIES:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=font-family:'Times New Roman'
'Times'
'serif';font-size:10pt;text-align:justify;margin:0pt;&gt;&lt;span style=visibility:hidden;&gt;&#x200b;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=font-family:'Times New Roman'
'Times'
'serif';font-size:10pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:18pt;margin:0pt;&gt;From time to time, the Company uses derivative instruments, including foreign currency forward contracts and commodity futures contracts to manage its exposures to foreign exchange and commodity prices. Commodity futures contracts are intended and effective as hedges of market price risks associated with the anticipated purchase of certain raw materials (primarily sugar). Foreign currency forward contracts are intended and effective as hedges of the Company&#x2019;s exposure to the variability of cash flows, primarily related to the foreign exchange rate changes of products manufactured in Canada and sold in the United States, and periodic equipment purchases from foreign suppliers denominated in a foreign currency. The Company does not engage in trading or other speculative use of derivative instruments.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=font-family:'Times New Roman'
'Times'
'serif';font-size:10pt;text-align:justify;margin:0pt;&gt;&lt;span style=visibility:hidden;&gt;&#x200b;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=font-family:'Times New Roman'
'Times'
'serif';font-size:10pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:18pt;margin:0pt;&gt;The Company recognizes all derivative instruments as either assets or liabilities at fair value in the Consolidated Statements of Financial Position. Derivative assets are recorded in other receivables and derivative liabilities are recorded in accrued liabilities. The Company uses either hedge accounting or mark-to-market accounting for its derivative instruments. Derivatives that qualify for hedge accounting are designated as cash flow hedges by formally documenting the hedge relationships, including identification of the hedging instruments, the hedged items and other critical terms, as well as the Company&#x2019;s risk management objectives and strategies for undertaking the hedge transaction.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=font-family:'Times New Roman'
'Times'
'serif';font-size:10pt;text-align:justify;margin:0pt;&gt;&lt;span style=visibility:hidden;&gt;&#x200b;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=font-family:'Times New Roman'
'Times'
'serif';font-size:10pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:18pt;margin:0pt;&gt;Changes in the fair value of the Company&#x2019;s cash flow hedges are recorded in accumulated other comprehensive loss, net of tax, and are reclassified to earnings in the periods in which earnings are affected by the hedged item. Substantially all amounts reported in accumulated other comprehensive loss for commodity derivatives are expected to be reclassified to cost of goods sold. Approximately $941 of this accumulated comprehensive gain is expected to be charged to earnings in 2021. Approximately $390 and $388 in accumulated other comprehensive gain for foreign currency derivatives is expected to be reclassified to other income, net in 2021 and 2022, respectively.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=font-family:'Times New Roman'
'Times'
'serif';font-size:10pt;text-align:justify;margin:0pt;&gt;&lt;span style=visibility:hidden;&gt;&#x200b;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=font-family:'Times New Roman'
'Times'
'serif';font-size:10pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:18pt;margin:0pt;&gt;The following table summarizes the Company&#x2019;s outstanding derivative contracts and their effects on its Consolidated Statements of Financial Position at December&#160;31, 2020 and 2019:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=font-family:'Times New Roman'
'Times'

'serif';font-size:10pt;text-align:justify;margin:0pt;&gt;Note 14 &#x2014; LEASES: &#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=background-color:#ffffff;font-family:'Times New Roman'
'Times'
'serif';font-size:10pt;text-align:justify;margin:0pt;&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;visibility:hidden;&gt;&#x200b;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=background-color:#ffffff;font-family:'Times New Roman'
'Times'
'serif';font-size:10pt;text-align:justify;margin:0pt;&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;The Company leases certain buildings, land and equipment that are classified as operating leases. These leases have remaining lease terms of up to approximately&#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;3 years&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;.&#160;In the fourth quarter and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=-sec-ix-hidden:Hidden_obqkqoMPe0yyNn1Kmxhteg;&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;font-family:'Times New Roman'
'Times'
'serif';font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;text-align:justify;&gt;twelve months&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt; of &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=-sec-ix-hidden:Hidden_HBdG_PfgJkSWXwr2NPGi-w;&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;font-family:'Times New Roman'
'Times'
'serif';font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;text-align:justify;&gt;2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt; and 2019, operating lease cost and cash paid for operating lease liabilities totaled &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;$271&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt; and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;$258&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;, respectively, and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;$1,023&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt; and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;$1,004&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;, respectively, which is classified in cash flows from operating activities. As of &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=-sec-ix-hidden:Hidden_VPNif6GHU0ujqnmdDPNUJA;&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;font-family:'Times New Roman'
'Times'
'serif';font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;text-align:justify;&gt;December 31, 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt; and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=-sec-ix-hidden:Hidden_KnpppT7jykmxL79n6ihO6g;&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;font-family:'Times New Roman'
'Times'
'serif';font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;text-align:justify;&gt;2019&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;, operating lease right-of-use assets and operating lease liabilities were &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=-sec-ix-hidden:Hidden_7hRJy8zbjUeK6acqOvdRBg;&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;font-family:'Times New Roman'
'Times'
'serif';font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;text-align:justify;&gt;both&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;$858&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=-sec-ix-hidden:Hidden_9SxUmgQHc0WO9e6E5mY1Qw;&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;font-family:'Times New Roman'
'Times'
'serif';font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;text-align:justify;&gt;and&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;$1,580&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;, respectively. The weighted-average remaining lease term related to these operating leases was&#160;approximately &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;0.7&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt; years and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;1.6&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;&#160;years as of December 31, 2020 and 2019, respectively. The weighted-average discount rate related to the Company&#x2019;s operating leases was&#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;3.0%&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt; and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;3.1%&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt; as of December 31, 2020 and 2019, respectively. Maturities of operating lease liabilities at December 31, 2020 are as follows: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;$717&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;&#160;in 2021, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;$137&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;&#160;in 2022, and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;$4&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt; in 2023.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=background-color:#ffffff;font-family:'Times New Roman'
'Times'
'serif';font-size:10pt;text-align:justify;margin:0pt;&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;visibility:hidden;&gt;&#x200b;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=background-color:#ffffff;font-family:'Times New Roman'
'Times'
'serif';font-size:10pt;text-align:justify;margin:0pt;&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;The Company, as lessor, rents certain commercial real estate to third party lessees. The December 31, 2020 and 2019 cost related to these leased properties was &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;$51,426&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;&#160;and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;$36,378&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;, respectively, and the accumulated depreciation related to these leased properties was &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;$14,784&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt; and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;$10,252&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;, respectively. Terms of certain such leases, including&#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=-sec-ix-hidden:Hidden_hr99PCyrpkqeLoz_WgS6dg;&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;font-family:'Times New Roman'
'Times'
'serif';font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;text-align:justify;&gt;renewal&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt; options, may be extended for up to&#160;approximately &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;sixty years&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;, many of which provide for periodic adjustment of rent payments based on changes in consumer or other price indices. The Company recognizes lease income on a straight-line basis over the lease term. Lease income in fourth quarter and twelve months 2020 and 2019 was &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;$863&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;&#160;and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;$718&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;, respectively, and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;$3,191&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt; and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;$2,951&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=color:#212529;&gt;, respectively, and is classified in cash flows from operating activities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=background-color:#ffffff;font-family:'Times New Roman'
'Times'
&lt;p style=font-family:'Times New Roman'
'Times'
